sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M34576
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part combines the arsenic transport genes and the photochelatin synthase gene from Arabadopsis Thaliana. Coupled with the Arsenic resistance pathway, this part is designed to complex and transport arsenic into a vacuole.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shambhu Koirala, Nathan Kipniss, Tyler Wagner
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The largest issue is the promoter being used- it really should be a promoter that is designed to work in plants. Finding a promoter that works in plants, but is sensitive to arsenic concentrations has almost impossible. The same can be said about the RBS and terminating sequences- ideally, these would be plant specific as well.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K165000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The is a repressable promoter for use in Saccharomyces cerevisiae. It is repressed by the presence of methionine. When unrepresssed, is has a moderate level of activity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From the Saccharomyces cerevisiae genome, by way of Caroline Ajo-Franklin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M34569
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Coding Sequence for Phytochelatin Synthase found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Polychelatins are a polymer of glutathione that are used stress responses to toxins. The phytochelatins bind to the toxins (commonly heavy metal toxins like Arsenic) and are then transported in to the vacuole in order to isolate the toxins from important components in the cytosol such as vital proteins and organelles.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nathan Kipniss, Tyler Wagner, Shambhu Koirala
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Unwanted restriction sites had to be removed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M34572
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Coding Sequence for Arsenic Transport 1 found in Arabadopsis Thaliana
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part takes an arsenic-phytochelatin complex and transports it into the vacuole. That way, arsenic does not interfere with important processes in the cell (like glycolysis, which arsenic can shut down).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nathan Kipniss, Tyler Wagner, Shambhu Koirala
